On Thu, Nov 4, 2010 at 1:29 AM, Mike Soultanian <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

> I would also test the sensors through the cable to the ecu, that way you
 know it's a good signal through the cable and back to ground (if it's
 grounded on the other end).  I would also spray ProGold on every electrical
 connection in your bus.  I make a habit of doing that as much as possible to
 keep all the connections clean.

This is a good point. Just as the computer depends on correct fuel
pressure to supply the correct amount of fuel, it also depends on
correct voltages.

Bad connections can degrade voltage and give false readings to the
computer, whether in the FI wiring connections or the vehicle main
voltages.

John
